- A month is assumed to be a period of 30 days; 
- Average temperature and humidity can indicate the overall climate of a location; 
- The number of unique users who accessed a weather data entry can be a measure of its popularity.

- Average temperature, humidity, sea level pressure, and wind speed are often used to understand the general weather conditions at a location; 
- Data quality can range from high (accurate and reliable) to low (less accurate or incomplete); 
- A higher level in the weather station hierarchy could imply a more generalized or aggregated view of the data.
